Lanxess to Invest 200 Million Euros in Singapore Rubber Plant

-- B y   A n d r e a   T a n
-- 
2011-06-01T07:00:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-01/lanxess-to-invest-200-million-euros-in-singapore-rubber-plant.html
Lanxess AG (LXS)  will invest 200 million
euros to build a neodymium polybutadiene rubber plant in
 Singapore , which it says will be the largest such facility in
the world.  The plant will be able to produce 140,000 metric tons of
the rubber, which is used in tires, each year, the Leverkusen,
Germany-based company said in a statement distributed in
Singapore today. The plant, which will start operations in 2015,
will employ 100 workers, the company said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andrea Tan in Singapore at 
 atan17@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sean Collins at 
 scollins14@bloomberg.net  